*IN DEVELOPMENT* 
u-Kama is designed to fail forward: 
each failure is retained as structural memory, 
tightening future constraint and reducing discretion, 
so that truth accumulates even when implementations do not endure.

Why? Ecosystems do not “bounce back”.
They either:
	•	adapt under constraint
	•	simplify
	•	or collapse and reassemble

u-Kama mirrors this honestly:
	•	no resurrection without loss
	•	no recovery without memory
	•	no rebirth without narrower possibility

That is not metaphor.
That is fidelity.
